{"id":285903238,"title":"A Bayesian non-parametric approach to asymmetric dynamic conditional correlation model with application to portfolio selection","authors":["Audronė Virbickaitė","Concepción Ausín","Pedro Galeano"],"_abstract":"ABSTRACT A Bayesian non-parametric approach for modeling the distribution of multiple returns is proposed. More specifically, an asymmetric dynamic conditional correlation (ADCC) model is considered to estimate the time-varying correlations of financial returns where the individual volatilities are driven by GJR-GARCH models. This composite model takes into consideration the asymmetries in individual assets’ volatilities, as well as in the correlations. The errors are modeled using a Dirichlet location–scale mixture of multivariate Normals allowing for a flexible return distribution in terms of skewness and kurtosis. This gives rise to a Bayesian non-parametric ADCC (BNP-ADCC) model, as opposed to a symmetric specification, called BNP-DCC. Then these two models are compared using a sample of Apple Inc. and NASDAQ Industrial index daily returns. The obtained results reveal that for this particular data set the BNP-ADCC outperforms the BNP-DCC model. Finally, an illustrative asset allocation exercise is presented.","cited_in":[],"reference":["https://www.researchgate.net/publication/222696680_Bayesian_estimation_of_the_Gaussian_mixture_GARCH_model","https://www.researchgate.net/publication/23948434_Multivariate_GARCH_models_a_survey","https://www.researchgate.net/publication/4857460_'ARCH_Modelling_in_Finance_A_Review_of_the_Theory_and_Empirical_Evidence'","https://www.researchgate.net/publication/45257636_Arch_models","https://www.researchgate.net/publication/4856560_Generalized_Conditional_Heteroscedasticity","https://www.researchgate.net/publication/4889230_Asymmetric_Dynamics_in_the_Correlation_of_Global_Equity_and_Bond_Returns","https://www.researchgate.net/publication/4895208_Autoregressive_Conditional_Heteroskedasticity_With_Estim